<task id="068" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Smoke remediation: Bug 1 (chat box) + UX-A (Recent Conversations) + UX-B (all wizards as popups)</title>
    <phase>F (Verification — remediation)</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-hours>2.5</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>020, 021, 023, 025, 042, 067, 070</dependencies>
    <blocks>071, 072, 073</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, ui-cleanup, refactoring, ux</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Three concurrent UI changes in SpaarkeAi affecting smoke-blocking issues. Touches ConversationPane.tsx, WelcomePanel.tsx, and ContextPaneController.tsx. Each change must preserve existing functionality on the non-affected paths. Code-review + ADR check applies.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Three changes touch different files but each requires verifying the whole welcome flow renders correctly. Single coordinated agent is cleaner than parallel.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Apply 3 smoke-remediation fixes to SpaarkeAi based on operator feedback (2026-05-20 smoke round 1):

    (Bug 1) Restructure ConversationPane welcome state so the chat input is visible — currently SprkChat is mutually exclusive with WelcomePanel.

    (UX-A) Remove the "Recent Conversations" section from WelcomePanel — pattern is "start blank; use History overlay to resume past sessions".

    (UX-B) Change GetStartedCards click handlers for Create Matter + Summarize Files to use Xrm.Navigation popup (matching the other 5 cards' pattern) instead of dispatching widget_load events that embed R2 widgets as Workspace tabs. Keep the embedded widgets registered in WorkspaceWidgetRegistry — they're still usable via direct widget_load from other parts of the system; we're just changing the ContextPaneController click-handler routing.

    Build + redeploy SpaarkeAi.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React + TypeScript engineer comfortable with SpaarkeAi solution layout, ConversationPane composition flow, and Xrm.Navigation dispatch patterns. Familiar with task 042's onCardClick wiring + task 045's AssignWorkWizardLauncher pattern.
  </role>

  <goal>
    After this task:
    - Assistant pane shows a usable chat input on cold load (Bug 1 resolved; FR-06 truly satisfied).
    - Welcome state contains ONLY "How can I help you today?" + the chat input (no Recent Conversations).
    - All 7 GetStartedCards uniformly use Xrm.Navigation popup (Create Matter + Summarize Files now match the other 5).
    - SpaarkeAi rebuilt + redeployed to dev.
    - Standalone LegalWorkspace and R2 widget consumers unaffected.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Smoke feedback identified:
      1. Assistant pane has no chat box. Diagnostic confirmed `ConversationPane.tsx` welcome-stage ternary mounts WelcomePanel OR SprkChat, never both. WelcomePanel only renders the "How can I help you today?" prompt + Recent Conversations; SprkChat (input owner) never mounts on cold load.
      2. Recent Conversations should be removed — pattern is "start blank; History overlay handles resume".
      3. UX consistency: 5/7 GetStartedCards already use Xrm.Navigation popups (Create Project, Find Similar, Send Email, Schedule Meeting, Assign Work). The remaining 2 (Create Matter, Summarize Files) dispatch widget_load events that mount embedded R2 wizard widgets as Workspace tabs. Operator wants all 7 consistent on popup pattern.

      Architectural note (preserved): R2 CreateMatterWizardWidget + DocumentUploadWizardWidget remain registered in WorkspaceWidgetRegistry. The embedded-tab structure stays available for other use cases (e.g., future R5 work). Only the CONTEXT-PANE click handlers change to dispatch popup navigation.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/ConversationPane.tsx</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/WelcomePanel.tsx</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/context/ContextPaneController.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/AssignWorkWizardLauncher.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/CreateMatterWizardWidget.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/DocumentUploadWizardWidget.tsx</file>
      <file>scripts/Deploy-SpaarkeAi.ps1</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-06 (input editable on cold load) MUST be functionally true after this task — chat input visible AND typeable BEFORE any session exists.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-25 / NFR-10: Standalone LegalWorkspace MUST continue to function identically. WelcomePanel.tsx + ConversationPane.tsx are SpaarkeAi-only; standalone LegalWorkspace doesn't consume them — verify nothing in ContextPaneController.tsx change leaks to standalone LegalWorkspace.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">No new shared-lib changes. All edits are SpaarkeAi-local.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">No new hex/rgba literals. Fluent v9 tokens only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 patterns.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No new accessToken props; all BFF calls (if any) via authenticatedFetch.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Do NOT delete or unregister CreateMatterWizardWidget / DocumentUploadWizardWidget from WorkspaceWidgetRegistry. They remain available for widget_load dispatch from non-ContextPane sources. Only change the click-handler routing in ContextPaneController.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Bug 1 fix must NOT add a SecondCopyOfWelcomePanel. The welcome content (prompt) lives ABOVE SprkChat in the same render path; SprkChat is always rendered; only the welcome content above is conditional on welcome stage.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
