    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Read current state">
      Read ConversationPane.tsx (especially lines ~687-929: showWelcomePanel logic, the ternary), WelcomePanel.tsx (the RecentConversationsSection + props), and ContextPaneController.tsx (the handleGetStartedCardClick handler from task 042).

      Also locate the Code Page webresource names for Create Matter + Summarize Files:
      - Grep for `sprk_creatematter` to find Create Matter Code Page name
      - Grep for `sprk_documentupload` or `sprk_document_upload` for Document Upload Code Page name
      - Confirm both exist as Dataverse web resources. If they don't exist as standalone Code Pages, STOP and report — embedded-only widgets can't be popup-launched without their Code Page being deployed.
    </step>

    <step order="2" name="Bug 1 fix — restructure ConversationPane welcome state">
      In `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/ConversationPane.tsx`:
      - Find the ternary at ~line 818: `{showWelcomePanel ? <WelcomePanel ... /> : <div ...><SprkChat /></div>}`
      - Replace with a structure where SprkChat is ALWAYS rendered, and welcome content sits above it when in welcome stage:
        ```tsx
        {showWelcomePanel && (
          <div className={styles.welcomeHeader}>
            <Text as="h2" size={400} weight="semibold">How can I help you today?</Text>
          </div>
        )}
        <div className={styles.chatRegion} role="region" aria-label="AI Chat">
          <SprkChat ... />
        </div>
        ```
      - Note: this REPLACES the dependence on WelcomePanel for the welcome content; WelcomePanel becomes a tiny shell or can be deleted. EVALUATE during implementation:
        - Option A: Keep WelcomePanel as a thin component containing just the heading + inline-rendered (no Recent Conversations); ConversationPane uses it as the welcome header content.
        - Option B: Inline the "How can I help you today?" Text directly in ConversationPane; delete WelcomePanel.tsx entirely.
        Prefer Option A if WelcomePanel is referenced elsewhere; Option B if it's only used by ConversationPane post-cleanup.
      - Add appropriate makeStyles entries (welcomeHeader: padding + center alignment via Fluent v9 tokens).
    </step>

    <step order="3" name="UX-A fix — remove Recent Conversations">
      In WelcomePanel.tsx (or wherever the welcome content lives after step 2):
      - Remove `RecentConversationsSection` import.
      - Remove the JSX block that renders `<RecentConversationsSection ... />`.
      - Remove the `useRecentSessions` hook call if it's no longer used elsewhere.
      - Remove related styles (recentSessionCard, etc.) if no longer needed.
      - Update the file header JSDoc to reflect the new welcome content (just the heading + chat input).
      - DO NOT delete RecentConversationsSection.tsx or its hook — they may be used by HistoryOverlay (task 022) or other consumers. Just remove from WelcomePanel.
    </step>

    <step order="4" name="UX-B fix — Create Matter + Summarize Files use Xrm.Navigation">
      In ContextPaneController.tsx, find handleGetStartedCardClick (task 042's wiring).

      Currently the switch (or if-else) dispatches widget_load for:
      - 'create-matter' → widget_load with 'create-matter-wizard'
      - 'summarize-files' (or 'document-upload') → widget_load with 'document-upload-wizard'

      Change to dispatch Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo (matching the pattern from task 045 AssignWorkWizardLauncher):
      - 'create-matter' → navigateTo({ pageType: 'webresource', webresourceName: 'sprk_creatematterwizard', data: 'bffBaseUrl=...' })
      - 'summarize-files' → navigateTo({ pageType: 'webresource', webresourceName: 'sprk_documentuploadwizard' (or the correct name from step 1 grep), data: 'bffBaseUrl=...' })

      Use the feature-detect + fallback pattern from AssignWorkWizardLauncher (window.Xrm check, return status object if absent, calling site decides UI fallback).

      RECOMMENDED implementation:
      - Either extend AssignWorkWizardLauncher into a generic "launchCodePageWizard(webresourceName, options)" helper in @spaarke/ai-widgets,
      - OR inline the Xrm.Navigation call directly in handleGetStartedCardClick (smaller blast radius; consistent with how SendEmail/MeetingSchedule were handled).
      Prefer the inline approach if it matches the existing pattern from task 042.

      KEEP CreateMatterWizardWidget + DocumentUploadWizardWidget registered in WorkspaceWidgetRegistry. Do NOT remove their registrations or source files. Only change how ContextPaneController routes the click.
    </step>

    <step order="5" name="Build + lint">
      - `cd src/solutions/SpaarkeAi && npm run build` — verify clean
      - Optionally `cd src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components && npm run build` if any shared-lib code was touched (should not be)
      - Verify dark-mode tokens still compliant (no hex/rgba introduced)
      - Capture new SpaarkeAi bundle size (expected: SLIGHTLY SMALLER due to removed RecentConversations imports — note delta)
    </step>

    <step order="6" name="Redeploy SpaarkeAi">
      Run `scripts/Deploy-SpaarkeAi.ps1` (no parameters — defaults to dev). Capture output. Confirm web resource sprk_spaarkeai updated + customizations published.
    </step>

    <step order="7" name="Update deploy memo">
      Append a "Supplemental Deploy — Task 068" section to `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/deploys/2026-05-20-deploy.md`:
      - What was deployed (sprk_spaarkeai)
      - Why (Bug 1 + UX-A + UX-B remediation per smoke feedback)
      - Bundle size delta
      - Deploy timestamp
    </step>

    <step order="8" name="Update task status + TASK-INDEX">
      - Task 068 POML → completed
      - TASK-INDEX row 068 → ✅
      - Update plan.md Risk Register: note Bug 1 + UX-A + UX-B RESOLVED in this task
    </step>
  </steps>

